<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - INSTALL - LEFT COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>LEFT COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the left countershaft assembly to the rear and insert the countershaft support tool or
                blocking to center the shaft in the rear case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021i0">Figure 180</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021i0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021i0" filename="../figg13/G13021I0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 180. Left Countershaft Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged end bearing driver to start the bearing in the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021i1">Figure 181</hotlnk>). Center the countershaft in the bearing and complete the
                installation.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021i1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021i1" filename="../figg13/G13021I1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 181. Center Countershaft In Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the retainer plate on the front of the left countershaft, roll pin in the hole at
                the end of the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021i2">Figure 182</hotlnk>). Secure with a bolt and tighten to 90 to 120 ft-lbs. (122
                to 163 N&#8226; m) when the shaft can be secured.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021i2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021i2" filename="../figg13/G13021I2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 182. Position Retainer Plate</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft support tool or blocking from the rear case bore and install the
                left countershaft rear bearing with the larger I.D. lead chamfer to the front of the shaft and install
                the snap ring in the groove at the rear of the left countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021i3">Figure 183</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021i3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021i3" filename="../figg13/G13021I3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 183. Install Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
